                    Pandora’s Worrisome Sign: Return of the Founder as C.E.O.                
Technology companies that turn back to their creators have a mixed track record.











                    Pandora Is Said to Have Held Talks About Selling Itself                
Pandora, whose stock has fallen more than 60 percent since October, is said to be working with Morgan Stanley to meet with potential buyers.
By LESLIE PICKER and BEN SISARIO













Tech Tip

                    Finding a Replacement for Free iTunes Radio                
Apple may have shut down its free streaming radio feature, but other free online stations are available.











                    Streaming Royalties Rise, but Not as High as Music Industry Wanted                
A panel of federal judges directed free Internet radio services like Pandora to pay 17 cents per 100 plays, less than the 25 cents record companies had sought.











                    For Pandora, Ruling on Streaming Royalty Rates Is Crucial                
An increase in the rates that webcasters, including Pandora, must pay record companies for the next five years may have huge consequences for Pandora’s business.
By BEN SISARIO













